        {
          "block_label": "header",
          "block_content": "6)Calculusand Number Theory ",
          "block_bbox": [
            1539,
            68,
            2219,
            134
          ],
          "block_id": 1,
          "block_order": null
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "Proof Firstly, from (9.14) we get ",
          "block_bbox": [
            164,
            190,
            1011,
            266
          ],
          "block_id": 2,
          "block_order": 1
        },
        {
          "block_label": "formula",
          "block_content": "\\begin{align*}\\left|P_n-\\sum_{k=1}^n\\frac{\\mu(k)}{k^2}\\right|&=\\left|\\sum_{k=1}^n\\mu(k)\\left(\\frac{1}{n^2}\\left\\lfloor\\frac{n}{k}\\right\\rfloor^2-\\frac{1}{k^2}\\right)\\right|\\\\&\\leq\\sum_{k=1}^n\\left|\\frac{1}{k^2}-\\frac{1}{n^2}\\left\\lfloor\\frac{n}{k}\\right\\rfloor^2\\right|.\\end{align*}",
          "block_bbox": [
            493,
            339,
            1739,
            762
          ],
          "block_id": 3,
          "block_order": 2
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "In order to estimate the last sum above, we claim that, given natural numbers n and k such that $1\\leq k\\leq n$ , we have \n",
          "block_bbox": [
            191,
            834,
            2239,
            960
          ],
          "block_id": 4,
          "block_order": 3
        },
        {
          "block_label": "formula",
          "block_content": "\\left|\\frac{1}{k^2}-\\frac{1}{n^2}\\left\\lfloor\\frac{n}{k}\\right\\rfloor^2\\right|<\\frac{2}{nk}-\\frac{1}{n^2}.",
          "block_bbox": [
            851,
            1026,
            1602,
            1168
          ],
          "block_id": 5,
          "block_order": 4
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "Indeed,",
          "block_bbox": [
            195,
            1237,
            388,
            1291
          ],
          "block_id": 6,
          "block_order": 5
        },
        {
          "block_label": "formula",
          "block_content": "\\begin{aligned}\\frac{n}{k}-1<\\left\\lfloor\\frac{n}{k}\\right\\rfloor\\leq\\frac{n}{k}&\\Rightarrow\\frac{n^2}{k^2}-\\frac{2n}{k}+1<\\left\\lfloor\\frac{n}{k}\\right\\rfloor^2\\leq\\frac{n^2}{k^2}\\\\&\\Rightarrow\\frac{1}{k^2}-\\frac{2}{kn}+\\frac{1}{n^2}<\\frac{1}{n^2}\\left\\lfloor\\frac{n}{k}\\right\\rfloor^2\\leq\\frac{1}{k^2}\\\\&\\Rightarrow0\\leq\\frac{1}{k^2}-\\frac{1}{n^2}\\left\\lfloor\\frac{n}{k}\\right\\rfloor^2<\\frac{2}{kn}-\\frac{1}{n^2},\\end{aligned}",
          "block_bbox": [
            512,
            1371,
            1973,
            1872
          ],
          "block_id": 7,
          "block_order": 6
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "as wished.",
          "block_bbox": [
            194,
            1929,
            463,
            1977
          ],
          "block_id": 8,
          "block_order": 7
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "Back to (9.15), we obtain from the above estimates that ",
          "block_bbox": [
            271,
            2005,
            1685,
            2066
          ],
          "block_id": 9,
          "block_order": 8
        },
        {
          "block_label": "formula",
          "block_content": "\\left|P_{n}-\\sum_{k=1}^{n}\\frac{\\mu(k)}{k^{2}}\\right|<\\sum_{k=1}^{n}\\left(\\frac{2}{nk}-\\frac{1}{n^{2}}\\right)=\\frac{2}{n}\\sum_{k=1}^{n}\\frac{1}{k}-\\frac{1}{n}.",
          "block_bbox": [
            562,
            2136,
            1946,
            2337
          ],
          "block_id": 10,
          "block_order": 9
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "Now, from L'Hôpital's rule we get ",
          "block_bbox": [
            203,
            2394,
            1077,
            2469
          ],
          "block_id": 11,
          "block_order": 10
        },
        {
          "block_label": "formula",
          "block_content": "\\frac{2}{n}\\sum_{k=1}^{n}\\frac{1}{k}<\\frac{2}{n}\\left(1+\\int_{1}^{n}\\frac{1}{t}dt\\right)=\\frac{2}{n}(\\log n+1)\\rightarrow0.",
          "block_bbox": [
            592,
            2549,
            1926,
            2736
          ],
          "block_id": 12,
          "block_order": 11
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "as $n\\rightarrow+\\infty$ . Hence,",
          "block_bbox": [
            204,
            2810,
            734,
            2870
          ],
          "block_id": 13,
          "block_order": 12
        },
        {
          "block_label": "formula",
          "block_content": "\\lim_{n\\to+\\infty}\\left(\\frac{2}{n}\\sum_{k=1}^{n}\\frac{1}{k}-\\frac{1}{n}\\right)=0,",
          "block_bbox": [
            873,
            2942,
            1637,
            3133
          ],
          "block_id": 14,
          "block_order": 13
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "and our previous estimates assure that ",
          "block_bbox": [
            204,
            3207,
            1164,
            3274
          ],
          "block_id": 15,
          "block_order": 14
        },
        {
          "block_label": "formula_number",
          "block_content": "(9.15)",
          "block_bbox": [
            2084,
            548,
            2225,
            605
          ],
          "block_id": 16,
          "block_order": null
        }
      ],
      "markdown": "Proof Firstly, from (9.14) we get \n\n$$\\begin{align*}\\left|P_n-\\sum_{k=1}^n\\frac{\\mu(k)}{k^2}\\right|&=\\left|\\sum_{k=1}^n\\mu(k)\\left(\\frac{1}{n^2}\\left\\lfloor\\frac{n}{k}\\right\\rfloor^2-\\frac{1}{k^2}\\right)\\right|\\\\&\\leq\\sum_{k=1}^n\\left|\\frac{1}{k^2}-\\frac{1}{n^2}\\left\\lfloor\\frac{n}{k}\\right\\rfloor^2\\right|.\\end{align*}$$\n\nIn order to estimate the last sum above, we claim that, given natural numbers n and k such that $1\\leq k\\leq n$ , we have \n\n\n\n$$\\left|\\frac{1}{k^2}-\\frac{1}{n^2}\\left\\lfloor\\frac{n}{k}\\right\\rfloor^2\\right|<\\frac{2}{nk}-\\frac{1}{n^2}.$$\n\nIndeed,\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\\frac{n}{k}-1<\\left\\lfloor\\frac{n}{k}\\right\\rfloor\\leq\\frac{n}{k}&\\Rightarrow\\frac{n^2}{k^2}-\\frac{2n}{k}+1<\\left\\lfloor\\frac{n}{k}\\right\\rfloor^2\\leq\\frac{n^2}{k^2}\\\\&\\Rightarrow\\frac{1}{k^2}-\\frac{2}{kn}+\\frac{1}{n^2}<\\frac{1}{n^2}\\left\\lfloor\\frac{n}{k}\\right\\rfloor^2\\leq\\frac{1}{k^2}\\\\&\\Rightarrow0\\leq\\frac{1}{k^2}-\\frac{1}{n^2}\\left\\lfloor\\frac{n}{k}\\right\\rfloor^2<\\frac{2}{kn}-\\frac{1}{n^2},\\end{aligned}$$\n\nas wished.\n\nBack to (9.15), we obtain from the above estimates that \n\n$$\\left|P_{n}-\\sum_{k=1}^{n}\\frac{\\mu(k)}{k^{2}}\\right|<\\sum_{k=1}^{n}\\left(\\frac{2}{nk}-\\frac{1}{n^{2}}\\right)=\\frac{2}{n}\\sum_{k=1}^{n}\\frac{1}{k}-\\frac{1}{n}.$$\n\nNow, from L'Hôpital's rule we get \n\n$$\\frac{2}{n}\\sum_{k=1}^{n}\\frac{1}{k}<\\frac{2}{n}\\left(1+\\int_{1}^{n}\\frac{1}{t}dt\\right)=\\frac{2}{n}(\\log n+1)\\rightarrow0.$$\n\nas $n\\rightarrow+\\infty$ . Hence,\n\n$$\\lim_{n\\to+\\infty}\\left(\\frac{2}{n}\\sum_{k=1}^{n}\\frac{1}{k}-\\frac{1}{n}\\right)=0,$$\n\nand our previous estimates assure that ",
